    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A form of very high resolution scanning probe microscopy in which a sample in solution is moved under an atomically sharp (i.e. only a few atoms wide) stylus mounted on a cantilevered spring. A detector senses deflections of the cantilever, measuring the force between stylus and surface, and transmits this information to an electronic display system.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
